AUDIO: 'The goal of the plugin is to make 3D Gaussian splats feel like any other asset would. Our holy grail has been always to make the artist feel this they\'re using just another asset. &gt;&gt; Relighting Gaussian splats is now possible. And today we are going deep on'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what it actually takes to bring this technology into real film and virtual production workflow. I\'m here with Fernando, CEO and co-founder of Volinga AI. Fernando initiated the early research that later became Volinga, a'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'company building professional tools for creating, editing, and rendering 3D Gaussian splats for film and virtual production. And now Volinga covered the full pipeline from reconstruction and editing to what I believe is the most'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'powerful relighting solution for 3D GS in Unreal Engine. We start by breaking down exactly how relighting works on Gaussian splats and why it is not as simple as flipping a switch. &gt;&gt; If you capture the splats and you have'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shadows on it, that\'s what we\'re calling this additive lighting because you are just adding on top of what you have. &gt;&gt; We also get into what it takes to process Gaussian splats at a level that meets Hollywood standards. &gt;&gt; With Volinga Suite, you have the full'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'flexibility, but also the full complexity of building your own your own capture system, which also makes this very, very powerful for the media entertainment industry. &gt;&gt; We look at the adoption challenges and how that looks like today.'

